WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.390
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:36.391 --> 00:37.475
EPISODE 9

00:37.476 --> 00:39.226
Hello, this is the restaurant, Naum.

00:39.227 --> 00:41.354
We found your pen while cleaning.

00:41.355 --> 00:45.399
If you ever find it,
can you contact me through this number?

00:45.400 --> 00:49.403
I remembered that you asked us
to contact you if we ever found it.

00:54.701 --> 00:57.287
I think you owe me an explanation.

01:13.095 --> 01:15.304
The location of the engraving,
and the font.

01:15.305 --> 01:17.390
Both of them are my pen.

01:17.391 --> 01:18.558
How can this happen?

01:19.810 --> 01:20.811
I…

01:22.062 --> 01:23.896
I bought it before.

01:23.897 --> 01:24.940
What do you mean?

01:25.691 --> 01:27.108
How could you have--

01:27.109 --> 01:28.402
I bought the same pen

01:30.612 --> 01:32.197
when I was in the States.

01:33.824 --> 01:36.325
When I first ran into you at the atelier,

01:36.326 --> 01:38.953
I was shocked when I saw your pen

01:38.954 --> 01:40.914
because it was so familiar.

01:46.128 --> 01:48.796
So you bought it when you returned
to the States?

01:48.797 --> 01:49.923
You got the same one?

01:51.716 --> 01:52.717
Yes.

01:56.555 --> 01:59.599
You should've told me.
I was so confused when I got this.

02:01.560 --> 02:04.354
I thought it was a special pen
made just for me,

02:05.313 --> 02:07.357
but I guess it's common in the US.

02:09.025 --> 02:10.734
You could've said you bought it.

02:10.735 --> 02:12.571
Did you think I'd feel uncomfortable?

02:13.989 --> 02:17.450
You really are an artist,
paying attention to so much detail.

02:17.451 --> 02:19.119
The engraving's exactly the same.

02:19.703 --> 02:23.915
It's just like you to go
and buy another one for me.

02:26.084 --> 02:27.127
I'm sorry.

02:29.004 --> 02:30.005
I…

02:35.010 --> 02:36.218
lied to you.

02:36.219 --> 02:38.095
You did it for me.

02:38.096 --> 02:39.598
I'll use it well. Thank you.

02:40.640 --> 02:42.266
It might be an ordinary pen,

02:42.267 --> 02:45.145
but the thought
behind buying it for me is special.

02:45.937 --> 02:47.105
So thank you.

02:50.442 --> 02:52.234
What is it this time?

02:52.235 --> 02:54.196
What on earth is going on with you?

02:59.242 --> 03:00.326
Mmm...

03:00.327 --> 03:01.453
You caught me.

03:04.998 --> 03:06.373
I'm going to France soon.

03:06.374 --> 03:07.626
France?

03:08.752 --> 03:09.835
When?

03:09.836 --> 03:12.129
Probably before spring.

03:14.049 --> 03:15.133
Spring?

03:16.343 --> 03:20.429
I was planning on retiring and going there
when I was around 60.

03:20.430 --> 03:23.642
But my plans got postponed
because of my daughter and son-in-law.

03:24.684 --> 03:27.270
I haven't told the kids yet,

03:28.897 --> 03:30.731
but I really want a break now.

03:30.732 --> 03:33.944
I've been working my butt off
for the past 50 years.

03:34.945 --> 03:35.946
Is that…

03:36.821 --> 03:37.822
really it?

03:38.281 --> 03:39.365
Of course.

03:40.450 --> 03:42.452
I wish I'd reunited with you sooner.

03:43.662 --> 03:44.663
It's just too bad.

03:45.956 --> 03:47.958
I have a lot on my mind these days.

03:48.458 --> 03:50.459
There's so much
to take care of before I go.

03:50.460 --> 03:52.628
That's why I wanted to go
to Chuncheon soon.

03:52.629 --> 03:53.797
Why did you go to the hospital?

03:55.340 --> 03:56.799
You weren't visiting a friend.

03:56.800 --> 03:59.469
I saw a nurse…

04:01.513 --> 04:02.596
calling your name.

04:04.099 --> 04:06.685
You think it's easy
managing a company until this age?

04:07.185 --> 04:10.312
My health is my asset,
so I get regular checkups.

04:10.313 --> 04:11.648
I just didn't want you to worry.

04:12.899 --> 04:15.151
Anyway, let's go to Chuncheon soon.

04:17.320 --> 04:20.490
I wonder if our house is still there.

04:41.887 --> 04:43.263
This is it.

05:22.802 --> 05:24.637
You did it for me.

05:24.638 --> 05:25.931
So thank you.

05:26.723 --> 05:30.684
The more you gain with deception,

05:30.685 --> 05:32.770
the less you can truly gain.

05:32.771 --> 05:34.939
It may seem like
you're gaining something now,

05:34.940 --> 05:37.399
but you'll probably end up
paying the price for it.

06:30.370 --> 06:31.371
The price…

06:42.340 --> 06:44.341
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

06:45.719 --> 06:48.053
Gosh, that's hot! I almost died.

06:50.181 --> 06:51.349
Be quiet…

07:04.487 --> 07:05.612
The porridge.

07:14.748 --> 07:15.749
Ms. Song?

07:16.458 --> 07:18.459
You're awake.

07:18.460 --> 07:19.877
- What are you doing here?
-  Uh...

07:19.878 --> 07:22.504
I came to drop off some documents,

07:22.505 --> 07:24.047
but I guess you don't remember.

07:24.048 --> 07:25.467
Are you feeling better?

07:26.050 --> 07:27.176
What is all this?

07:27.177 --> 07:31.096
How can you only have water
and candy at home?

07:31.097 --> 07:34.684
So I ordered some pots
and dishes and stuff.

07:35.143 --> 07:36.561
Delivery is awesome in Korea!

07:37.437 --> 07:38.938
Sit down. The porridge is done.

07:39.439 --> 07:41.524
It's late. You should go.

07:42.108 --> 07:43.317
I'll take you--

07:43.318 --> 07:45.153
Don't be silly. You're sick.

07:47.197 --> 07:51.492
There's nothing more miserable
than being alone when you're sick.

07:51.493 --> 07:53.077
So stay right here.

07:53.620 --> 07:55.622
Ah, pardon me for a moment.

07:57.582 --> 07:59.333
Okay. Your fever dropped.

07:59.334 --> 08:02.545
The pear tea's almost done, too.
It's the best for a cold.

08:05.131 --> 08:07.508
I don't think I should see Hayeong.

08:07.509 --> 08:09.135
She kept talking about you.

08:09.844 --> 08:11.429
I think she likes you a lot.

08:13.097 --> 08:14.640
Really?

08:14.641 --> 08:17.351
- Top of his year the whole time?
- Yes. The entire time.

08:17.352 --> 08:19.228
Wow. He was a genius.

08:19.229 --> 08:21.563
His nickname was Yeon Taeseop,

08:21.564 --> 08:24.066
like Song Taeseop from Slam Dunk.

08:25.151 --> 08:28.403
Yeon Taeseop? So?
Did he enter competitions and stuff?

08:28.404 --> 08:30.698
Of course. For competitions, he…

08:32.283 --> 08:34.911
Here. Unfortunately,
I can't guarantee the taste.

08:36.746 --> 08:38.163
I'll eat it when you leave.

08:38.164 --> 08:40.332
- It's late, so--
- No.

08:40.333 --> 08:42.335
I'll leave after I see you
finishing the bowl.

08:43.294 --> 08:47.464
You were the one who told me
to be honest if I wasn't okay.

08:47.465 --> 08:49.717
Why didn't you tell me you were sick?

08:50.385 --> 08:51.386
I…

08:52.470 --> 08:54.346
shouldn't be sick.

08:54.347 --> 08:55.430
Huh?

08:55.431 --> 08:57.391
Why would anyone
not be allowed to be sick?

08:57.392 --> 08:58.601
You just have to get better.

08:59.435 --> 09:00.562
Eat up before it gets cold.

09:02.313 --> 09:03.314
All right.

09:09.821 --> 09:10.822
Mr. Yeon.

09:11.447 --> 09:13.867
I'll get straight to the point.

09:14.951 --> 09:17.829
I've been getting my hopes up these days.

09:18.788 --> 09:21.416
I thought you were blushing and sweating

09:22.250 --> 09:25.627
because you had feelings for me.
I didn't know you were sick.

09:25.628 --> 09:28.131
But to be honest,

09:29.090 --> 09:30.091
I was happy.

09:31.759 --> 09:35.846
Mr. Yeon, even seeing you with bedhead
makes me curious.

09:35.847 --> 09:39.183
I find myself overthinking
everything you do or say.

09:39.184 --> 09:41.477
And it hurts to see you sick.

09:41.936 --> 09:44.271
I guess I've been denying my feelings,

09:44.272 --> 09:46.149
but I'm sure of it now.

09:46.858 --> 09:48.567
- Mr. Yeon.
- Ms. Song.

09:48.568 --> 09:50.235
I think I like you.

09:50.236 --> 09:51.696
No, I'm sure I like you.

09:57.327 --> 09:58.328
If…

09:59.329 --> 10:01.956
I gave you the wrong idea, I'm sorry.

10:03.416 --> 10:06.628
But I've never thought of you…

10:08.880 --> 10:10.130
as more than a colleague.

10:10.131 --> 10:11.799
Yes, of course.

10:12.425 --> 10:13.717
I thought so.

10:13.718 --> 10:14.885
Mmm...

10:14.886 --> 10:15.887
Then…

10:17.847 --> 10:19.306
start thinking of me that way.

10:22.185 --> 10:26.355
I guess you'll only eat comfortably
once I'm gone.

10:26.356 --> 10:30.275
Then I hope you get well soon.

10:30.276 --> 10:31.736
I'll see you at work.

10:34.072 --> 10:35.447
Ms. Song.

10:45.792 --> 10:48.503
Don't forget
to take this three times a day.

10:56.219 --> 10:57.428
I must be crazy.

10:58.137 --> 10:59.639
I told him I like him.

11:01.432 --> 11:04.269
But it's fine.
I was just telling him the truth.

11:05.186 --> 11:06.479
Good job, Song Hayeong.

11:09.440 --> 11:11.401
What do I do?

11:30.962 --> 11:32.797
Please let Yougyum…

11:34.257 --> 11:36.050
be okay.

11:37.760 --> 11:39.052
Please…

11:39.053 --> 11:40.805
Good job, Yougyum.

11:41.639 --> 11:44.182
Yougyum, your foot.

11:47.103 --> 11:48.104
What did they say?

11:51.065 --> 11:52.858
I've recovered.

11:52.859 --> 11:55.278
I'll be perfectly healed
after some treatment.

11:56.154 --> 11:58.239
It must have swollen from exhaustion.

11:58.823 --> 12:00.742
I'll be fine in a week.

12:00.867 --> 12:03.702
You must have been shocked.

12:05.413 --> 12:06.998
I'm so relieved.

12:07.790 --> 12:10.042
You were in the nurse's office
because of your foot, right?

12:10.043 --> 12:12.169
It was my fault.

12:12.170 --> 12:14.796
I misunderstood and threw a fit,

12:14.797 --> 12:16.840
and I made you worry about me.

12:16.841 --> 12:18.592
Goodness.

12:18.593 --> 12:20.803
I thought you were smart,
but you were a fool.

12:21.512 --> 12:22.804
That's nonsense.

12:22.805 --> 12:25.599
I thought you wouldn't
be able to play baseball again.

12:25.600 --> 12:27.809
Hadam! It's an emergency. Get up.

12:27.810 --> 12:30.312
What is it? Is your foot hurting?

12:30.313 --> 12:31.439
No.

12:32.273 --> 12:36.109
You're wasting your time here
when the CSAT is just around the corner.

12:36.110 --> 12:38.779
Hurry home and get some rest.

12:38.780 --> 12:40.530
I'm going to nurse you.

12:40.531 --> 12:41.657
Really?

12:42.283 --> 12:44.577
Then I should go home
instead of getting treated.

12:45.244 --> 12:47.704
Okay, fine. I'll go.

12:47.705 --> 12:51.917
Don't worry, and focus on the CSAT.
We'll take good care of him.

12:51.918 --> 12:55.045
Don't think about coming before the exams.
I won't even let you in.

12:55.046 --> 12:58.173
I'll get plenty of rest
and receive treatment.

12:58.174 --> 13:00.300
So let's meet after the exams, okay?

13:02.011 --> 13:03.261
Focus!

13:03.262 --> 13:04.722
Focus.

13:07.016 --> 13:09.559
I want you in charge of this.

13:09.560 --> 13:11.645
The overall visuals
for a fashion editorial?

13:11.646 --> 13:13.271
You always did this yourself…

13:13.272 --> 13:16.233
This shoot is about showcasing
the brand's identity.

13:16.234 --> 13:19.862
It's about time
we aligned it with your pace.

13:20.488 --> 13:23.448
Plan the mood, color scheme,
and the flow of the looks.

13:23.449 --> 13:26.201
As you said, we're showcasing
the brand's overall tone.

13:26.202 --> 13:27.285
You should handle--

13:27.286 --> 13:29.747
What do you think, Mr. Yeon?
Will it be hard for her?

13:30.331 --> 13:32.916
I believe she can do it.

13:32.917 --> 13:35.210
I'll support you with anything you need.

13:35.211 --> 13:36.670
Okay. Then that's done.

13:36.671 --> 13:41.424
From now on, prioritize Ms. Song's opinion
when adjusting colors and quantities.

13:41.425 --> 13:44.177
What? Ms. Kim…

13:44.178 --> 13:45.470
Why are you--

13:45.471 --> 13:46.889
Don't make me repeat myself.

13:47.723 --> 13:49.933
You should take some of my workload.

13:49.934 --> 13:51.811
Let me get some rest, too.

13:52.395 --> 13:55.272
Ah. And clear my schedule
for a day this week.

13:55.273 --> 13:56.524
- Is there something…
- What…

13:58.067 --> 13:59.110
Go ahead.

14:00.153 --> 14:01.278
Is something wrong?

14:01.279 --> 14:03.280
You never asked
to clear a schedule before.

14:03.281 --> 14:06.950
It's just that I want some fresh air
before it gets too cold.

14:06.951 --> 14:09.245
- Then I'll take you--
- It's fine. I can go on my own.

14:10.913 --> 14:12.080
Yes, ma'am.

14:12.081 --> 14:13.248
But, Ms. Kim,

14:13.249 --> 14:14.916
I really don't think I should do--

14:14.917 --> 14:16.085
Meeting's over.

14:27.471 --> 14:29.015
Will I have enough time?

14:30.433 --> 14:31.434
No.

14:32.852 --> 14:34.520
I have to get it done.

14:40.735 --> 14:43.070
Uh, she has a personal appointment.

14:43.613 --> 14:46.032
All right.
Please postpone it to next week.

14:49.118 --> 14:51.078
Good afternoon.

14:51.913 --> 14:53.456
Are you feeling better?

14:54.248 --> 14:55.875
Yes, thanks to you.

15:02.882 --> 15:06.510
Song Hayeong, age 29, ENFP.
And ENFJ when I'm working.

15:07.053 --> 15:10.972
I like my family, friends,
colleagues, work, driving,

15:10.973 --> 15:12.974
listening to music while walking
on a windy day,

15:12.975 --> 15:14.309
being honest, tasty food,

15:14.310 --> 15:15.769
especially snack bar food.

15:15.770 --> 15:18.146
Mmm... And watching
cute videos before bed.

15:19.774 --> 15:21.441
- What?
- And what I don't like

15:21.442 --> 15:22.943
are people who are frustrating,

15:22.944 --> 15:26.321
cowardly, who pick on the weak,
stir up conflict, snitch, get paranoid.

15:26.322 --> 15:27.948
And I hate losing people I love,

15:27.949 --> 15:29.700
seeing them in pain...

15:30.243 --> 15:32.370
Ah, and mosquitoes.

15:33.829 --> 15:36.915
Oh, and I forgot one.

15:36.916 --> 15:40.711
Recently, something was added
to the list of things I like.

15:43.089 --> 15:45.925
What are you doing?

15:48.302 --> 15:50.470
We don't know much
about each other personally,

15:50.471 --> 15:52.264
even after all these years.

15:52.265 --> 15:55.684
I told you to think about me,
but I thought you wouldn't have much info,

15:55.685 --> 15:57.270
so I gave you some.

16:03.526 --> 16:05.402
Ah, I'm not pressuring you.

16:05.403 --> 16:08.905
You're always serious and prudent,
so you can take your time.

16:08.906 --> 16:10.615
It's all right with me.

16:10.616 --> 16:14.160
But everyone ends up liking me
the more they get to know me.

16:14.161 --> 16:16.580
I'm just saying.

16:17.707 --> 16:21.209
Having personal conversations
like this at work isn't really…

16:22.878 --> 16:26.382
Mr. Yeon doesn't like
personal conversations at work.

16:27.258 --> 16:28.466
Okay.

16:28.467 --> 16:31.304
I just acquired
some more info about you.

16:32.179 --> 16:34.140
Then have a good day.

16:42.481 --> 16:44.649
So, what do you think about this scene?

16:44.650 --> 16:47.360
Um...
Yeah, I mean, it's good overall.

16:47.361 --> 16:48.903
A few things here and there
we could tweak.

16:48.904 --> 16:51.740
Oh! Ben, how have you been?

16:51.741 --> 16:54.200
I've been doing very well.

16:54.201 --> 16:57.495
My mother-in-law's food is amazing.

16:57.496 --> 17:01.167
We were having a meeting
because we got the additional script.

17:01.709 --> 17:03.668
We'll send it to the design team later.

17:03.669 --> 17:05.963
All right. I'll let you work.

17:07.298 --> 17:08.299
Hi.

17:09.133 --> 17:10.134
Sounds good.

17:15.556 --> 17:16.681
Good meeting.

17:18.267 --> 17:19.934
Should I raise the neckline a bit?

17:22.938 --> 17:24.397
Mr. Park, the coffee.

17:24.398 --> 17:25.482
Oh, gosh.

17:25.483 --> 17:26.484
Goodness.

17:27.818 --> 17:29.320
Uh, were you looking at this pen?

17:30.237 --> 17:32.739
Mr. Seonu bought this for me.

17:32.740 --> 17:34.824
This must be common in the States.

17:34.825 --> 17:37.410
He got it for me
when he went back last time.

17:37.411 --> 17:39.537
He even put a lucky sticker on it.

17:39.538 --> 17:41.206
Right…

17:41.207 --> 17:43.793
I'm glad you like it.

17:58.849 --> 18:00.392
I guess you like Bach.

18:00.393 --> 18:03.853
No. I just happened
to hear about the song.

18:03.854 --> 18:07.149
Someone told me it's good for insomnia.

18:17.118 --> 18:18.536
The music is a bit sad.

18:19.078 --> 18:21.330
I should change it to a brighter song.

18:35.886 --> 18:38.139
Let her feel joy again.

18:39.181 --> 18:42.685
Tell me anything. I'll be your safe space.

18:50.651 --> 18:52.902
Ta-da! I'm getting perfect scores.

18:52.903 --> 18:54.404
I'm going to nail the CSAT.

18:54.405 --> 18:57.240
How are you feeling? Is the food okay?

18:57.241 --> 19:00.285
Ta-da! I'm cleaning
all my plates, and I'm in great condition!

19:00.286 --> 19:02.288
Don't worry about me and focus.

19:02.955 --> 19:04.289
Hmm!

19:04.290 --> 19:05.291
Right. Focus.

19:08.544 --> 19:10.587
"Won flew through the night sky.

19:10.588 --> 19:14.549
"Below her, the Milky Way
was pouring down like a river."

19:14.550 --> 19:16.092
Milky Way…

19:16.093 --> 19:18.554
Won flew through the night sky.

19:19.096 --> 19:24.560
Below her, the Milky Way
was pouring down like a river.

19:41.160 --> 19:42.243
Hmm?

19:42.244 --> 19:44.746
RAN

19:44.747 --> 19:46.080
You haven't gone to bed?

19:46.081 --> 19:47.248
Not yet.

19:50.628 --> 19:52.086
But what are you up to?

19:52.087 --> 19:54.423
There's a newly added scene
of the Milky Way,

19:55.049 --> 19:56.634
so I wanted to go see it.

19:57.384 --> 19:58.511
Should we…

20:00.012 --> 20:02.138
Oh, it's pretty late.

20:02.139 --> 20:03.891
Driving alone at this hour?

20:04.558 --> 20:08.019
That's not fair. We promised
to work through your list together.

20:08.020 --> 20:09.979
Stargazing was on your list.

20:09.980 --> 20:13.274
Going alone doesn't count.
I'll take my car and head there.

20:13.275 --> 20:14.360
So just wait.

20:17.071 --> 20:20.449
I guess the moon's in a good mood today.

20:20.991 --> 20:23.451
We won't be able to see the Milky Way
if it's so bright.

20:23.452 --> 20:24.661
Hmm?

20:24.662 --> 20:26.580
We can't see it because of the moon?

20:27.206 --> 20:29.166
The moon's pretty bright,

20:29.792 --> 20:33.462
so faint lights like the Milky Way
get washed out by the light.

20:34.046 --> 20:35.713
Oh...

20:37.258 --> 20:38.259
It's cold, isn't it?

20:38.759 --> 20:40.052
Sorry, it's my fault.

20:41.762 --> 20:43.389
Uh, can we use that?

20:47.059 --> 20:48.060
- Here.
- Thanks.

20:50.980 --> 20:52.564
Let's just go.

20:52.565 --> 20:54.483
We'll come back
when the moon's less bright.

20:55.734 --> 20:56.986
Oh!

21:23.637 --> 21:26.140
It's so beautiful.

21:39.737 --> 21:42.656
I feel like I'm in space.

21:43.782 --> 21:45.951
I feel like I'm in a dream.

22:07.473 --> 22:08.557
But…

22:09.850 --> 22:12.770
those words sounded a bit sad.

22:14.271 --> 22:17.106
The Milky Way being visible
when there's no moon.

22:19.026 --> 22:22.780
The moon and the Milky Way
go so well together.

22:24.323 --> 22:29.411
It sounds like
they're not meant to be together.

22:31.163 --> 22:34.333
Hmm... That's a bit sad.

22:35.918 --> 22:39.630
I feel like I'll never be able

22:40.255 --> 22:42.215
...to forget this moment.

22:43.509 --> 22:45.844
I've never really liked winter...

23:01.568 --> 23:02.652
Don't you think so?

23:04.488 --> 23:05.571
Hmm?

23:05.572 --> 23:06.948
You were distracted, weren't you?

23:06.949 --> 23:09.909
Sorry.

23:09.910 --> 23:13.746
The stars and the person next to me

23:13.747 --> 23:14.999
were so beautiful

23:15.833 --> 23:18.084
that I spaced out for a moment.

23:19.211 --> 23:20.379
Gosh.

23:22.172 --> 23:25.175
I said I won't ever forget

23:25.926 --> 23:27.886
this moment.

23:29.763 --> 23:32.433
Ah, and in spring…

23:33.434 --> 23:35.352
Uh, will you not be here in spring?

23:38.897 --> 23:39.898
Anyway,

23:40.941 --> 23:41.942
thank you

23:42.818 --> 23:44.570
for showing me such a beautiful sky.

24:03.630 --> 24:06.591
You're back late. You look tired.

24:06.592 --> 24:07.884
Go and rest.

24:07.885 --> 24:09.344
Goodnight.

24:15.726 --> 24:16.727
Mr. Park.

24:17.770 --> 24:18.771
Yes?

24:19.730 --> 24:20.731
I…

24:22.566 --> 24:24.276
want to stay by her side

24:26.028 --> 24:28.739
in spring, in summer,

24:30.949 --> 24:32.450
in fall, and in winter.

24:36.080 --> 24:37.331
I want…

24:41.502 --> 24:43.545
to stay by her side,

24:46.590 --> 24:48.342
but I don't know what to do.

24:58.185 --> 24:59.353
Do you need someone

25:00.437 --> 25:01.563
to talk to?

25:21.834 --> 25:23.627
"Surrounded by walls"?

25:26.380 --> 25:27.839
You saved me as well.

25:27.840 --> 25:29.508
Neon alien…

25:53.031 --> 25:58.829
SUMMER, SEVEN YEARS AGO
IT STARTED WITH WALLS

26:08.255 --> 26:10.591
I heard you going out late last night.

26:11.091 --> 26:13.092
Were you meeting Chan?

26:13.093 --> 26:14.719
Just for a bit.

26:14.720 --> 26:18.557
Why did you meet at that hour?
Were you making out?

26:19.099 --> 26:20.142
Does it show?

26:21.310 --> 26:23.102
Goodness.

26:23.103 --> 26:24.770
No, not at all.

26:24.771 --> 26:26.397
Good job. Make out as much as you want.

26:28.275 --> 26:30.151
You're coming downstairs already?

26:30.152 --> 26:32.028
Did you not get enough sleep?

26:32.029 --> 26:34.656
I did, I went to bed
at 9:00p.m. last night.

26:35.407 --> 26:38.827
But what's going on here?

26:39.620 --> 26:42.747
Ta-da. We're making you
a lunchbox for your CSAT.

26:42.748 --> 26:46.250
We've been planning the menu
for the past three days.

26:46.251 --> 26:48.878
Will it be safe to eat?

26:48.879 --> 26:51.380
- Of course.
- I can just buy gimbap.

26:51.381 --> 26:53.674
Mom would scold us harshly
if you did that.

26:53.675 --> 26:55.468
Hang on. We just have to heat the soup.

26:55.469 --> 26:57.553
I have to go now, though.

26:57.554 --> 26:58.846
There's plenty of time.

26:58.847 --> 27:01.432
I want to visit Yougyum at the hospital
before I go.

27:01.433 --> 27:03.643
Hospital? Yougyum's in the hospital?

27:03.644 --> 27:06.188
He told me not to say anything…

27:08.857 --> 27:11.609
He's hospitalized because of his foot.

27:11.610 --> 27:12.777
Was he hurt badly?

27:12.778 --> 27:14.362
He's a baseball player--

27:14.363 --> 27:16.657
He said he'll get better
with some treatment,

27:17.532 --> 27:18.616
but I'm worried.

27:20.160 --> 27:22.912
Anyway, he's my good luck charm,

27:22.913 --> 27:26.040
so I feel like I should see him
before the CSAT to do well.

27:26.041 --> 27:28.043
Hang on. I'll pack something for him, too.

27:28.752 --> 27:31.004
Hadam, come here for a moment.

27:31.755 --> 27:34.758
Sit down. I'll tie your hair for you.

27:35.801 --> 27:36.884
That's so random.

27:38.845 --> 27:40.472
When you have a lot on your mind,

27:41.306 --> 27:43.266
brushing your hair calmly

27:43.850 --> 27:45.978
will help you relax.

27:49.272 --> 27:51.441
Yougyum will get through it,

27:52.150 --> 27:56.029
and don't forget
that you're perfectly prepared.

28:01.410 --> 28:02.827
You look beautiful.

28:04.538 --> 28:07.082
Of course. I'm your granddaughter.

28:10.669 --> 28:12.004
Don't worry.

28:12.587 --> 28:16.133
I'm your granddaughter,
and Haran and Hayeong's little sister.

28:17.009 --> 28:18.801
I'll do well.

28:18.802 --> 28:20.428
We can take you.

28:20.429 --> 28:23.682
It's really fine.
I want to do this on my own.

28:25.058 --> 28:27.351
Our baby is all grown up
and taking the CSAT.

28:27.352 --> 28:28.853
Did you prepare

28:28.854 --> 28:30.646
your OMR marker and a clock?

28:30.647 --> 28:32.690
Markers, clocks, and hand warmers.

28:32.691 --> 28:36.069
You and even Mr. Yeon
gave me a whole heap of them.

28:36.653 --> 28:39.447
She should go now.
Come on, let's give her some strength.

28:40.532 --> 28:42.576
Strength.

28:47.372 --> 28:49.624
He said I shouldn't come before the CSAT.

28:50.459 --> 28:52.377
But I have to see him, no matter what.

28:54.129 --> 28:56.672
The surgery is at 8:30 a.m.

28:56.673 --> 29:00.052
and we'll fill the top of the foot
with bone taken from the pelvis.

29:00.802 --> 29:01.887
Surgery?

29:04.598 --> 29:06.891
- You're getting surgery?
- Hadam.

29:06.892 --> 29:08.434
You said it'll get better soon.

29:08.435 --> 29:10.979
Would a bone graft heal in just a week?

29:11.480 --> 29:14.191
I'm sorry. Can I talk to my friend
for just a moment?

29:17.486 --> 29:19.863
It must have hurt so much.

29:20.489 --> 29:23.365
Why didn't you tell me anything?

29:23.366 --> 29:26.411
How could I do that
when you're facing something so important?

29:27.204 --> 29:29.205
I'm okay, so go take the exams.

29:29.206 --> 29:30.207
No,

29:31.249 --> 29:33.418
the most important thing to me is you.

29:34.002 --> 29:35.128
I'm staying by your side.

29:35.712 --> 29:36.962
Hadam.

29:36.963 --> 29:39.632
How can I focus on my exams
when you're getting surgery?

29:39.633 --> 29:42.052
I can enter college a year late.

29:42.636 --> 29:44.804
You can just take the bone from my pelvis.

29:44.805 --> 29:47.139
You play sports, but I just sit and study.

29:47.140 --> 29:48.183
This is why

29:48.934 --> 29:50.560
I couldn't tell you.

29:51.561 --> 29:54.230
If you do this, I can't keep seeing you.

29:54.231 --> 29:58.443
- I can take the CSAT next year.
-  No, that's not okay with me.

29:59.027 --> 30:00.028
I…

30:01.655 --> 30:03.657
want to be able to face you without guilt.

30:08.286 --> 30:09.370
What do we do?

30:09.371 --> 30:15.168
What if you end up
not being able to play baseball?

30:16.753 --> 30:17.754
Hadam.

30:19.047 --> 30:20.173
Give me your hand.

30:25.262 --> 30:28.681
I'll recover perfectly
and be back on the mound soon.

30:28.682 --> 30:30.142
I'm just taking a short breather.

30:30.934 --> 30:32.226
You saw my room, right?

30:32.227 --> 30:35.730
My life's goal is to be someone
you can be proud of.

30:40.277 --> 30:44.405
Let's both focus on our own paths
and meet in a few hours.

30:44.406 --> 30:46.198
Come see me after the exams.

30:46.199 --> 30:47.367
You can do that, right?

30:56.334 --> 30:58.544
I'll distribute the exam papers now.

30:58.545 --> 31:01.631
Take one and pass them back.

31:21.067 --> 31:25.405
Please let Yougyum's surgery go well.

31:27.574 --> 31:31.702
Please let Hadam do well on the exam.

31:34.623 --> 31:36.374
Let's begin the test.

31:50.764 --> 31:53.140
SURGERY IN PROGRESS

31:55.644 --> 31:56.770
Good morning.

31:57.896 --> 31:59.481
And thank you.

32:00.398 --> 32:04.652
You really are considerate.
You send Hadam a clock and OMR markers.

32:06.446 --> 32:07.655
What are you doing after work?

32:07.656 --> 32:09.823
I was thinking of getting snacks.

32:09.824 --> 32:11.533
If you're free…

32:11.534 --> 32:12.535
Ah. Take it.

32:17.999 --> 32:19.083
Yes, Mr. Chae.

32:19.084 --> 32:20.877
It's Mr. Chae?

32:22.254 --> 32:23.255
Just a moment.

32:24.923 --> 32:30.052
The materials company he mentioned
will do a material test in a few weeks.

32:30.053 --> 32:33.264
He wants to visit the factory,
and asked if we'll join.

32:33.265 --> 32:34.556
Of course, we should go.

32:34.557 --> 32:36.351
That's great.

32:37.018 --> 32:38.687
All right, we'll join you.

32:39.437 --> 32:40.563
Okay.

32:41.231 --> 32:42.565
Uh, and, Hyunwoo,

32:43.817 --> 32:47.487
the chance of Ms. Song and I dating…

32:48.321 --> 32:49.405
is zero.

32:51.116 --> 32:52.992
I thought I should tell you

32:52.993 --> 32:56.079
that there's no need to worry about that.

32:57.038 --> 32:58.039
Okay.

33:00.292 --> 33:03.211
I thought you'd keep waiting
for an answer.

33:04.462 --> 33:05.963
You don't have to waste

33:05.964 --> 33:07.674
your energy on me.

33:13.888 --> 33:14.889
Aren't you getting in?

33:15.974 --> 33:18.768
I left something at home, no, my car.

33:19.561 --> 33:20.854
All right, then.

33:31.197 --> 33:32.282
Zero…

33:35.869 --> 33:37.162
You're getting ready?

33:38.121 --> 33:39.164
Yes.

33:39.706 --> 33:41.416
I'll tell her everything

33:41.958 --> 33:44.377
and apologize to her.

33:44.836 --> 33:45.837
At this rate,

33:46.629 --> 33:48.839
I feel like I'll end up hiding more things

33:48.840 --> 33:51.551
and lying to her even more, so I'm scared.

33:52.135 --> 33:55.262
I want to tell her everything

33:55.263 --> 33:58.058
and love her as my true self from now on.

33:59.100 --> 34:02.519
I want to tell her in my own way
before it's too late.

34:02.520 --> 34:07.691
The interruption in your hearing
must be from the stress of lying, too.

34:07.692 --> 34:09.651
You know it yourself

34:09.652 --> 34:12.280
that the truth cannot coexist
with false relationships.

34:12.947 --> 34:16.533
It sounds like
they're not meant to be together.

34:16.534 --> 34:18.912
Like the Milky Way and the moon…

34:19.537 --> 34:22.122
These symptoms will occur
more frequently and intensely.

34:22.123 --> 34:24.208
It could end up hurting you badly.

34:24.209 --> 34:26.418
Let's stabilize your condition first.

34:26.419 --> 34:30.547
I'll prescribe a short-term
sedative for you. Ah...

34:30.548 --> 34:32.591
What did the new hallucination sound like?

34:32.592 --> 34:33.675
Ah.

34:33.676 --> 34:36.261
It was sharp, like the sound of metal.

34:36.262 --> 34:38.556
And then something…

34:39.474 --> 34:41.266
like this.

34:43.812 --> 34:46.313
I'm not exactly sure what it was.

34:46.314 --> 34:48.273
But I'm worried that...

34:48.274 --> 34:50.734
there's something more behind it.

34:50.735 --> 34:53.112
Like the bracelet sounds?

34:53.113 --> 34:56.740
Yes. And if I want
to tell her about myself,

34:56.741 --> 35:00.619
I think I should fill those gaps
in my memory first.

35:00.620 --> 35:01.955
She's connected...

35:04.082 --> 35:06.042
to what happened seven years ago.

35:06.751 --> 35:11.255
Your memories
are like scattered dots right now.

35:11.256 --> 35:14.466
They're not connected,
so you can't understand them.

35:14.467 --> 35:18.262
But once they start getting connected,

35:18.263 --> 35:20.473
they'll start forming a structure,
like this.

35:21.266 --> 35:23.016
And once the gaps are filled

35:23.017 --> 35:26.103
and you understand them yourself,
you'll be able--

35:26.104 --> 35:27.313
To explain myself

35:28.648 --> 35:30.859
to her better.

35:32.569 --> 35:36.322
Do you think there's a way
to fill those gaps?

35:38.408 --> 35:40.118
Mmm.

35:40.827 --> 35:42.203
I think so.

35:43.371 --> 35:45.956
Is there anyone else named Sujin

35:45.957 --> 35:49.293
among the staff besides Lee Sujin?

35:49.294 --> 35:50.420
Just a moment.

36:05.268 --> 36:06.936
The day of the accident?

36:07.604 --> 36:08.980
Why are you asking me that?

36:10.607 --> 36:12.608
I heard the explosion seven years ago

36:12.609 --> 36:15.570
in Hyeokchan's lab
was caused by a reagent error.

36:16.988 --> 36:18.656
I was just outside the door at the time.

36:20.033 --> 36:22.744
My memories are hazy from the shock.

36:23.870 --> 36:25.038
Do you remember what happened?

36:26.289 --> 36:28.208
I really want to protect something,

36:28.708 --> 36:29.709
but to do that,

36:31.336 --> 36:34.088
I need my memories.
I came to ask you for help.

36:34.881 --> 36:37.216
I wasn't even a student at your college.

36:37.217 --> 36:39.302
I was just a med student
at a school nearby.

36:40.011 --> 36:43.847
I only visited BIT a few times
to meet Hyeokchan, so why…

36:43.848 --> 36:45.808
Whenever I had glimpses
of my lost memories,

36:45.809 --> 36:48.393
I heard the same sound.

36:51.898 --> 36:54.483
Hey, Sujin. You're here?
I'll head out now.

36:54.484 --> 36:55.776
I heard the sound of your bracelet

36:55.777 --> 36:58.822
that you always wore
when you came to see Hyeokchan.

36:59.614 --> 37:00.989
It seemed like a sign

37:00.990 --> 37:04.994
that you're the person
who remembers everything.

37:08.540 --> 37:12.417
I don't know why the gaps in my memories
are connected to you,

37:12.418 --> 37:16.589
but can you tell me what you know
about what happened

37:17.841 --> 37:18.967
seven years ago that I don't?

37:22.846 --> 37:24.472
I wrote everything down

37:25.139 --> 37:26.850
whenever I had glimpses of the memories.

37:45.618 --> 37:48.245
- Stop it!
- I'm sorry.

37:48.246 --> 37:49.955
You're in a dangerous state.

37:49.956 --> 37:51.499
- I'm sorry.
- It's not too late.

37:55.670 --> 37:57.045
If there's anything you know…

37:57.046 --> 37:58.756
No, there's nothing.

37:59.340 --> 38:01.758
All I did was exchange
a few words with you.

38:01.759 --> 38:03.136
I'm sorry I couldn't help you.

38:04.220 --> 38:05.221
The sound.

38:06.264 --> 38:08.850
Do you know nothing
about the sound I wrote about?

38:09.475 --> 38:11.101
I think it's an important clue.

38:11.102 --> 38:12.185
Uh...

38:12.186 --> 38:15.022
It all started with a sound,
and all these memories--

38:15.023 --> 38:16.149
I said I don't know!

38:16.941 --> 38:18.985
What happened back then still hurts me.

38:19.611 --> 38:21.487
I lost Hyeokchan in that accident.

38:21.988 --> 38:24.824
What's going to change by digging into it?
Someone died.

38:25.783 --> 38:28.368
Why would you torture someone
over just some memories?

38:28.369 --> 38:30.746
You're alive and well right now.

38:30.747 --> 38:32.999
- I…
- I don't know anything,

38:33.541 --> 38:36.377
so don't ever look for me again.

38:46.346 --> 38:48.973
Hyeokchan, you left your earphones
in my car…

38:51.643 --> 38:52.644
So you're saying

38:53.311 --> 38:55.939
you kept talking to Haran

38:56.731 --> 38:57.732
while I was away?

38:58.316 --> 38:59.566
Pretending to be me?

38:59.567 --> 39:00.860
Stop it!

39:14.123 --> 39:17.000
Genius, won't this look lovely on Chan?

39:20.880 --> 39:22.048
You're so cute.

39:29.305 --> 39:30.722
Where were you?

39:30.723 --> 39:32.934
I didn't call in case you were
having a meeting with Ben.

39:39.065 --> 39:41.526
Hey, why don't you look happy to see me?

39:43.945 --> 39:47.824
I am. I'm so happy, I almost danced.

39:48.825 --> 39:50.283
Is something wrong?

39:50.284 --> 39:51.285
You look troubled.

39:54.956 --> 39:58.126
I was, because I missed you.

39:58.751 --> 39:59.919
But I came here,

40:00.420 --> 40:03.131
and you're right in front of me.

40:04.132 --> 40:06.092
Then look at me all you want.

40:15.351 --> 40:17.936
Oh. Why aren't you sitting
in your usual seat?

40:17.937 --> 40:20.981
You weren't here,
so I was waiting to see you coming.

40:20.982 --> 40:22.692
Like a meerkat.

40:23.276 --> 40:24.818
What did you sketch? Can I see?

40:26.070 --> 40:27.863
No, this…

40:27.864 --> 40:29.489
It's a trade secret.

40:32.827 --> 40:35.495
Let me take those.

40:35.496 --> 40:38.457
Customers have been asking for blankets,

40:38.458 --> 40:41.418
so I washed them.

40:41.419 --> 40:43.003
You should ask me to do chores.

40:43.004 --> 40:45.047
I should put these in the baskets, right?

40:45.048 --> 40:47.883
- Yes. Thank you.
- No problem.

40:47.884 --> 40:49.427
Hmm?

40:50.053 --> 40:51.261
Happy birthday.

40:51.262 --> 40:54.514
I'm flying out for a seminar,
so I wanted to say it a day early.

40:54.515 --> 40:56.433
I'll treat you for the watch soon.

40:56.434 --> 40:57.435
Birthday?

40:59.103 --> 41:00.354
I should make this soon.

41:01.939 --> 41:03.399
SHIM
Coffee House

41:04.192 --> 41:06.151
Keep your schedule cleared
tomorrow evening.

41:06.152 --> 41:08.320
We're going to dress up
and have a nice dinner.

41:08.321 --> 41:09.613
Sounds good.

41:09.614 --> 41:10.990
Uh, but why all of a sudden?

41:11.741 --> 41:15.285
Uh... I added dressing up

41:15.286 --> 41:17.788
and having a fancy dinner
to the bucket list.

41:17.789 --> 41:19.498
I'll treat you to everything,

41:19.499 --> 41:21.041
and tell you the location later.

41:21.042 --> 41:22.167
Hmm...

41:22.168 --> 41:25.421
- What's going on?
- Anyway, dress up, okay? See you.

41:27.298 --> 41:28.758
His size…

41:33.930 --> 41:34.931
This is out of the blue.

41:38.476 --> 41:39.559
Uh...

41:39.560 --> 41:42.980
I have a habit of saying goodbye
the American way.

41:44.482 --> 41:46.483
- Since when?
- Starting today.

41:47.610 --> 41:48.694
I'll get going now.

41:53.032 --> 41:54.492
Hmm?

41:57.120 --> 41:59.664
FATHER
HAPPY BIRTHDAY

42:04.168 --> 42:05.169
Gosh.

42:05.753 --> 42:07.171
That was way too obvious.

42:09.257 --> 42:13.010
Do you think there's a way
to fill those gaps?

42:30.611 --> 42:32.821
-  Hadam.
- Yougyum.

42:32.822 --> 42:34.782
How did you do?

42:36.492 --> 42:38.161
I nailed it.

42:39.078 --> 42:40.204
I kept my promise.

42:40.955 --> 42:42.123
I'm glad.

42:43.291 --> 42:45.418
I'm so glad.

42:45.960 --> 42:47.043
Thank you.

42:47.044 --> 42:49.087
They said the surgery went well.

42:49.088 --> 42:50.673
You did it.

42:51.257 --> 42:53.967
I keep feeling sleepy.

42:53.968 --> 42:54.969
Okay.

42:56.304 --> 42:58.014
Sleep. I'll stay with you.

43:01.809 --> 43:05.104
I'll recover perfectly
and be back on the mound soon.

43:21.495 --> 43:24.122
Oh, Mr. Yeon, we're heading out now.

43:24.123 --> 43:26.042
See you tomorrow.

43:26.709 --> 43:28.877
- See you tomorrow.
- You're working late again?

43:28.878 --> 43:30.046
Hang in there.

43:30.838 --> 43:33.465
I want to be on Hayeong's team!

43:33.466 --> 43:35.050
- Me too.
-  Me too, me too.

43:35.051 --> 43:36.134
Me too!

43:36.135 --> 43:38.220
You all want to pair up with me,
the bowling genius.

43:40.473 --> 43:41.848
Yes, Ms. Kim.

43:41.849 --> 43:45.185
You postponed the meeting
with Most Korea's editor-in-chief, right?

43:45.186 --> 43:47.563
Yes, I postponed it to next week.

43:48.731 --> 43:52.485
Sorry, but could I ask
where you're going tomorrow?

43:53.069 --> 43:54.486
- I should know
- I'm here…

43:54.487 --> 43:56.364
- to feel more at ease.
-  Chuncheon.

43:56.948 --> 43:58.406
I'm visiting my hometown.

43:58.407 --> 44:01.326
Don't worry, and call me
if anything urgent comes up.

44:01.327 --> 44:02.494
All right.

44:02.495 --> 44:03.578
You're here.

44:03.579 --> 44:05.664
You cleared your schedule
to go to Chuncheon?

44:05.665 --> 44:06.748
Why Chuncheon?

44:06.749 --> 44:08.167
I want to have some fun, too.

44:09.627 --> 44:12.672
I want to visit
our old neighborhood with Manjae.

44:13.256 --> 44:14.423
I see.

44:15.591 --> 44:17.176
What do you mean, "I see"?

44:18.469 --> 44:19.636
It's nothing.

44:19.637 --> 44:21.554
And you look good in all the scarves.

44:21.555 --> 44:23.266
Your beauty can pull off any color.

44:23.766 --> 44:25.893
But I like the one on the left.

44:26.769 --> 44:28.604
Keep smiling like that. You look pretty.

44:29.563 --> 44:31.857
It's rare to find someone
who makes you smile. Hold onto him.

44:40.199 --> 44:42.618
She has great taste.

44:43.953 --> 44:45.245
She really takes after me.

44:49.375 --> 44:50.960
Look at this.

44:51.669 --> 44:53.838
All right. Is this better?

44:57.425 --> 44:59.926
-  Or this?
-  I love you.

44:59.927 --> 45:03.763
I know. I love you, too.

45:03.764 --> 45:06.808
But I have to choose
which scarf to wear right now.

45:06.809 --> 45:08.977
Look at them again. Which is better?

45:08.978 --> 45:12.940
This train will soon arrive
at its final stop, Chuncheon Station.

45:17.028 --> 45:18.779
Everything's changed.

45:19.572 --> 45:21.239
I can't tell which is which.

45:23.200 --> 45:27.163
I think… this is where your house was.

45:28.122 --> 45:30.541
Yes, you're right.

45:32.251 --> 45:33.336
But…

45:34.170 --> 45:35.588
our house is gone.

45:36.547 --> 45:37.964
Gosh.

45:37.965 --> 45:39.717
It's been so many years.

45:42.136 --> 45:46.556
Right. Even we've changed this much,
so they can't possibly still be here.

45:48.726 --> 45:49.727
It's here!

45:50.686 --> 45:51.812
The tree's still here.

45:54.690 --> 45:57.317
You're right, it's still here.

45:57.318 --> 45:59.695
The persimmon tree my dad planted.

46:02.239 --> 46:03.449
I'm glad

46:04.658 --> 46:06.077
that's still here, at least.

46:14.919 --> 46:17.505
Nabong, let's go to school!

46:19.340 --> 46:21.549
I'm going to school!

46:21.550 --> 46:22.676
Manjae!

46:26.472 --> 46:28.724
- All right. Let's go.
- Hold on tight.

46:38.150 --> 46:39.442
Wow…

46:39.443 --> 46:42.153
It's right here.

46:42.154 --> 46:43.906
This tree is still here.

46:44.407 --> 46:45.657
It hasn't changed at all.

46:45.658 --> 46:47.909
Come on. Hurry.

46:49.161 --> 46:50.537
Right.

47:04.051 --> 47:05.218
This is so nice.

47:06.345 --> 47:09.348
Hmm... Hang on, it's untied.

47:10.057 --> 47:11.058
Mmm...

47:16.564 --> 47:18.482
Ah...  Have some water.

47:19.233 --> 47:21.318
- Manjae, there's something in here.
- Huh?

47:25.281 --> 47:27.992
I got you!

47:28.576 --> 47:31.578
Try and catch me.

47:45.176 --> 47:46.718
Manjae! My goodness.

47:46.719 --> 47:49.929
- I got my revenge.
- Unbelievable.

47:53.893 --> 47:56.311
Stay here. I'll go get something warm.

47:56.312 --> 47:57.396
- Okay.
- Okay.

48:34.934 --> 48:38.353
I must've startled you yesterday.
It was the anesthetics.

48:38.354 --> 48:41.105
I'm completely fine now.

48:41.106 --> 48:43.316
No, it's the painkillers.

48:43.317 --> 48:46.319
The second day of the bone graft
hurts the most.

48:46.320 --> 48:49.113
The pain in your pelvis
will probably get worse tomorrow,

48:49.114 --> 48:51.574
and you'll barely be able to walk
with crutches

48:51.575 --> 48:53.701
after the drain is removed
on the third day.

48:53.702 --> 48:54.828
- And--
- Wait.

48:55.412 --> 48:59.041
Did I wake after 10 years of sleep
or something?

48:59.625 --> 49:01.084
Did you become a doctor already?

49:01.085 --> 49:03.878
I studied about bone grafting all night.

49:03.879 --> 49:05.548
And here's your plan.

49:06.549 --> 49:07.550
What plan?

49:08.717 --> 49:12.638
A 12-week plan to pass
the New York Comets' physical.

49:13.097 --> 49:15.557
I'm going to help you
with your rehabilitation now.

49:15.558 --> 49:16.641
Huh?

49:16.642 --> 49:19.770
I did well on the CSAT,
and I have time on my hands.

49:20.271 --> 49:22.565
The first step is the hospital treatment.

49:23.065 --> 49:24.274
Focus on recovering,

49:24.275 --> 49:27.235
and once you can move, it's step two.

49:27.236 --> 49:28.445
You'd better brace yourself.

49:28.946 --> 49:30.738
I signed up for the study room again.

49:30.739 --> 49:33.284
I guess I'm getting practice
as a future medical professional.

49:35.327 --> 49:36.411
Yougyum!

49:36.412 --> 49:37.913
Hey!

49:39.623 --> 49:42.959
Why didn't you tell me
you were getting surgery?

49:42.960 --> 49:46.379
Should I give you some time alone?

49:46.380 --> 49:48.756
Hey, I'm getting a call.

49:52.469 --> 49:53.553
Hello?

49:53.554 --> 49:56.889
Hi, I saw this number
on this woman's necklace.

49:56.890 --> 50:00.226
She doesn't seem to know
where she is right now.

50:00.227 --> 50:02.812
I thought I should let you know.

50:02.813 --> 50:04.606
Uh, right. Just a moment.

50:07.735 --> 50:09.068
Can you buy me some tangerines?

50:09.069 --> 50:13.239
I'm suddenly craving them.
Maybe I need vitamins.

50:13.240 --> 50:14.490
Sure, I'll go buy some.

50:14.491 --> 50:17.035
Yang Changmo, come with me.

50:17.036 --> 50:19.037
I shouldn't leave you with him.

50:19.038 --> 50:22.166
Call me if you need anything else.
I'll get it for you.

50:25.044 --> 50:26.503
Where are you calling from?

50:28.422 --> 50:29.756
Chuncheon?

50:31.759 --> 50:35.678
Can you stay with her for a moment?
I'll call you back soon.

50:35.679 --> 50:38.890
Have you seen someone like this
on the way here?

50:38.891 --> 50:41.935
You didn't? All right, thank you.

50:46.607 --> 50:48.775
- Hello?
- Is this Hadam's grandmother's phone?

50:48.776 --> 50:51.486
Are you with Ms. Nana Kim right now?

50:51.487 --> 50:53.363
I'm her youngest
granddaughter's boyfriend.

50:53.364 --> 50:54.447
She was lost,

50:54.448 --> 50:56.825
so someone called and said she's with her.

50:57.534 --> 50:58.702
What?

51:00.412 --> 51:02.998
I'm the only one who knows her condition.

51:03.540 --> 51:06.167
Hadam and her sisters don't know yet.

51:06.168 --> 51:08.336
- Hello.
- I called you earlier…

51:08.337 --> 51:10.047
Ah. Over there.

51:12.091 --> 51:14.634
Ah, yes, thank you.

51:20.599 --> 51:21.600
Nabong.

51:29.024 --> 51:30.441
Ms. Kim Nabong!

51:30.442 --> 51:31.984
- Ms. Kim Nabong!
-  Wait, Na…

51:31.985 --> 51:33.654
I was just visiting a friend there.

51:34.405 --> 51:35.739
I'm going to France soon.

51:39.284 --> 51:40.411
That's what it was.

51:41.537 --> 51:43.664
This is what was happening

51:44.581 --> 51:45.748
to you.

51:52.131 --> 51:54.299
Nabong, come back to me.

51:54.800 --> 51:56.050
Huh?

51:56.051 --> 51:57.094
It's me,

51:57.803 --> 51:58.846
it's Manjae.

52:01.306 --> 52:02.433
I'm tired.

52:03.726 --> 52:05.435
I'm so tired.

52:05.436 --> 52:07.019
Okay, get some rest.

52:07.020 --> 52:08.897
Keep resting.

52:09.606 --> 52:10.691
Just rest.

52:32.963 --> 52:35.841
I booked a table here.
Come by 8:00 p.m.

52:36.759 --> 52:37.968
Hmm...

52:38.677 --> 52:40.887
Hmm...

52:40.888 --> 52:43.181
You always look nice,
but dress even nicer.

52:43.182 --> 52:44.767
This is it.

52:47.269 --> 52:49.520
You know it yourself

52:49.521 --> 52:52.316
that the truth cannot coexist
with false relationships.

52:56.653 --> 52:57.987
It's my friend's birthday.

52:57.988 --> 53:01.032
Can you bring that with the candles lit
for the dessert course?

53:02.951 --> 53:03.994
This much?

53:10.876 --> 53:13.337
Gosh, why does it keep falling?

53:38.403 --> 53:39.529
Your hand.

53:39.530 --> 53:41.030
Are you okay?

53:41.031 --> 53:43.325
Are you hurt anywhere?

53:44.618 --> 53:45.911
I'm fine.

53:49.623 --> 53:51.166
That's a relief.

53:53.293 --> 53:55.128
Ah. Are you okay?

53:55.712 --> 53:56.713
Yes...

54:00.717 --> 54:01.718
I'm fine.

54:08.308 --> 54:10.936
I'll clean up here. You should go.

54:11.603 --> 54:14.356
Don't work so late like you did yesterday.

54:30.289 --> 54:31.790
Let's talk for a moment.

54:45.012 --> 54:47.097
I'll be there in five minutes.
See you soon.

55:23.383 --> 55:26.053
I'm sorry, but that sound is bothering me.

55:28.555 --> 55:29.556
Sorry.

55:40.067 --> 55:41.942
It could end up hurting you badly.

55:41.943 --> 55:43.027
And in spring…

55:43.028 --> 55:45.821
It sounds like
they're not meant to be together.

55:45.822 --> 55:46.906
I don't know anything.

55:46.907 --> 55:49.493
You always look nice,
but dress even nicer.

56:21.608 --> 56:24.486
I feel like I should hear
your honest thoughts

56:25.362 --> 56:27.114
to be able to move on.

56:28.990 --> 56:30.908
I have a meeting tomorrow morning.

56:30.909 --> 56:33.119
I have some more work to do--

56:33.120 --> 56:34.829
Just have one glass.

56:34.830 --> 56:36.081
This could be

56:36.707 --> 56:38.125
the last time we talk like this.

56:49.344 --> 56:53.222
How did you know
I've been working late these days?

56:53.223 --> 56:56.392
I don't head out until all the lights
are turned off in the office.

56:56.393 --> 56:58.894
Then what about how you stopped the shelf…

56:58.895 --> 57:01.439
A designer's hands
are their greatest asset.

57:01.440 --> 57:04.775
I only did that to stop you
from getting hurt.

57:04.776 --> 57:07.571
Because I'm a designer at the atelier?

57:10.365 --> 57:11.449
Not because…

57:13.243 --> 57:15.287
I'm Song Hayeong?

57:21.835 --> 57:22.836
No.

57:30.886 --> 57:32.261
But, Mr. Yeon,

57:32.262 --> 57:33.597
I…

57:34.431 --> 57:36.266
keep misunderstanding such gestures.

57:37.768 --> 57:40.103
You got revenge on Cha Min for me,

57:40.604 --> 57:42.606
brushed off those leaves with your hands,

57:45.567 --> 57:48.779
and told me it's okay to say I'm not okay.

57:51.198 --> 57:53.700
I keep replaying those moments in my head.

57:54.576 --> 57:56.702
So I have to hear it today.

57:56.703 --> 58:00.040
This will keep going on
if I don't hear an honest answer.

58:01.583 --> 58:04.169
Am I really…

58:05.212 --> 58:06.922
just mistaken

58:08.173 --> 58:09.633
about all those situations?

58:12.219 --> 58:13.512
Ms. Kim

58:14.429 --> 58:16.056
is my savior.

58:16.932 --> 58:19.434
And her family, Haran, you,

58:20.268 --> 58:21.435
and Hadam,

58:21.436 --> 58:23.271
are precious to me, too.

58:24.689 --> 58:26.233
I have to protect all of you.

58:27.692 --> 58:29.735
That's why I took care of you.

58:29.736 --> 58:32.489
Even if Haran was in danger,

58:33.281 --> 58:34.533
I would've done the same.

58:35.909 --> 58:37.994
If those moments gave you the wrong idea,

58:39.287 --> 58:40.288
then I'm sorry.

58:43.917 --> 58:47.128
So I guess you're saying

58:48.046 --> 58:51.758
you don't see me as a woman at all.

58:53.760 --> 58:54.761
I'm sorry.

58:56.388 --> 59:00.141
Okay. If you're that firm about it,
then there's nothing I can do.

59:00.725 --> 59:02.726
I don't want to cause you trouble.

59:02.727 --> 59:06.522
I can easily move on and let this go.

59:06.523 --> 59:07.606
Easily.

59:10.443 --> 59:11.528
How about a handshake?

59:12.445 --> 59:15.781
Uh, it would be stupid
for us to grow awkward because of this.

59:15.782 --> 59:18.826
So let's shake hands to end this

59:18.827 --> 59:20.120
on good terms.

59:31.423 --> 59:34.551
You can go now.
You said you have a meeting.

59:35.927 --> 59:37.803
I'm going to eat some of this.

59:37.804 --> 59:40.015
My stomach's been growling for a while.

59:43.018 --> 59:44.227
I'll start the car now.

59:46.646 --> 59:48.064
Excuse me. Sir?

59:49.649 --> 59:50.900
Oh...

59:50.901 --> 59:52.944
Yes, please go.

01:00:02.203 --> 01:00:03.204
Sir.

01:00:04.039 --> 01:00:06.499
Sorry, but can you open the trunk?

01:01:01.012 --> 01:01:03.889
How did you hold out
with a fever close to 40 degrees?

01:01:03.890 --> 01:01:06.475
Once the meds kick in,
your fever should come down.

01:01:06.476 --> 01:01:07.643
Get some rest.

01:01:07.644 --> 01:01:08.645
Thank you.

01:01:09.604 --> 01:01:10.938
I'm sorry, Ms. Kim.

01:01:10.939 --> 01:01:13.399
I should've driven you on your trip,

01:01:13.400 --> 01:01:15.484
but I shouldn't drive in this state.

01:01:15.485 --> 01:01:18.655
I'll get better soon
and pick you up once your trip's over.

01:01:19.155 --> 01:01:20.364
I'm so sorry.

01:01:25.578 --> 01:01:27.872
DAUGHTER OF KIM NABONG
AND HER HUSBAND HAVE PASSED AWAY

01:01:32.919 --> 01:01:33.920
Sorry.

01:01:35.505 --> 01:01:37.339
I have to be okay.

01:01:37.340 --> 01:01:39.091
I have to keep our family together.

01:01:40.510 --> 01:01:41.720
I have to be okay.

01:01:42.470 --> 01:01:43.805
I have to be okay.

01:01:45.390 --> 01:01:46.433
It's my fault…

01:01:55.191 --> 01:01:56.276
I'm sorry.

01:01:59.696 --> 01:02:01.239
I'm really sorry.

01:02:10.415 --> 01:02:12.875
Where are you?
Why aren't you picking up?

01:02:12.876 --> 01:02:14.251
Did something happen?

01:02:14.252 --> 01:02:16.003
Why can't I reach you?

01:02:16.004 --> 01:02:17.337
I'm getting worried.

01:02:17.338 --> 01:02:19.632
Is there something wrong?

01:02:29.476 --> 01:02:30.477
Hello?

01:02:31.269 --> 01:02:32.270
Hello?

01:02:33.188 --> 01:02:34.230
Who is this?

01:02:49.454 --> 01:02:50.455
Hey.

01:02:50.997 --> 01:02:51.998
Did you cry?

01:02:52.916 --> 01:02:54.083
I'm okay.

01:02:54.084 --> 01:02:55.794
Let's go to the restaurant.

01:03:01.091 --> 01:03:02.549
I'm really fine.

01:03:02.550 --> 01:03:03.927
Why are you lying?

01:03:04.511 --> 01:03:05.595
You're not okay.

01:03:06.429 --> 01:03:08.098
I heard the doctors talking.

01:03:09.432 --> 01:03:11.684
What's inside your head?

01:03:16.898 --> 01:03:19.858
The shrapnel's still lodged deep
in the temporal bone.

01:03:19.859 --> 01:03:23.529
It's right next to the facial nerve,
so there's a high risk of nerve damage.

01:03:23.530 --> 01:03:25.697
These are the follow-up records.

01:03:25.698 --> 01:03:28.700
It went through the petrous part
and even involved the IAC.

01:03:28.701 --> 01:03:31.036
That's how he got his hearing loss.

01:03:31.037 --> 01:03:33.414
Was it the accident
where you lost your hearing?

01:03:34.415 --> 01:03:37.043
If there's something in there,
it's dangerous.

01:03:44.259 --> 01:03:46.802
I'm not someone who will leave
in three months,

01:03:46.803 --> 01:03:49.180
nor someone who might never come back.

01:03:49.889 --> 01:03:51.015
Ms. Song, I want to stay

01:03:52.475 --> 01:03:53.476
with you.

01:03:56.271 --> 01:03:57.855
No, Haran.

01:03:57.856 --> 01:03:59.148
So I'll tell you everything.

01:03:59.149 --> 01:04:01.860
I'll tell you all about the shrapnel
in my head, my ear,

01:04:03.153 --> 01:04:05.904
and about the scars on my body.

01:04:05.905 --> 01:04:07.240
I'll tell you what happened,

01:04:08.241 --> 01:04:11.577
But to tell you everything precisely,

01:04:11.578 --> 01:04:13.245
I need some time.

01:04:13.246 --> 01:04:14.581
It won't take long.

01:04:15.290 --> 01:04:18.251
I'll tell you everything honestly soon.

01:04:20.044 --> 01:04:22.088
I'll lay my heart bare.

01:04:23.173 --> 01:04:25.508
So when I do,

01:04:26.217 --> 01:04:27.676
please listen to everything.

01:04:29.429 --> 01:04:31.013
What if you're not okay?

01:04:31.014 --> 01:04:32.514
What if something else happens?

01:04:32.515 --> 01:04:35.726
I've been okay, I'm okay now,
and I'll keep being okay.

01:04:35.727 --> 01:04:36.728
So…

01:04:38.271 --> 01:04:39.314
let's go see

01:04:42.233 --> 01:04:44.152
the cherry blossoms in spring.

01:04:44.903 --> 01:04:47.696
We'll have shaved ice in summer,

01:04:47.697 --> 01:04:50.033
see the autumn leaves in fall,

01:04:50.700 --> 01:04:51.910
and in winter…

01:04:53.661 --> 01:04:55.830
it would be fun to go snowboarding.

01:04:58.416 --> 01:04:59.833
You're awake.

01:04:59.834 --> 01:05:01.711
Could you leave for a moment?

01:05:02.670 --> 01:05:03.755
Stop crying.

01:05:04.797 --> 01:05:06.674
I'll just get checked and leave soon.

01:05:11.221 --> 01:05:13.556
THE SURFACES, BORDERS,
AND TRANSMITTING STRUCTURES

01:05:17.143 --> 01:05:18.977
Are you okay?

01:05:18.978 --> 01:05:20.730
Gosh.

01:05:32.325 --> 01:05:33.909
No, just my roommate.

01:05:43.920 --> 01:05:45.630
-  Here.
- Thank you.

01:05:47.257 --> 01:05:49.092
I think you dropped your bracelet.

01:05:51.511 --> 01:05:52.804
This is yours, right?

01:06:05.733 --> 01:06:08.193
Oh. Hey, crybaby Song Haran!

01:06:12.282 --> 01:06:13.283
Hmm?

01:06:57.493 --> 01:07:00.413
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:07:24.562 --> 01:07:27.314
I'll make your birthday
even more special next year.

01:07:27.315 --> 01:07:30.193
I'm going to use that trial
for the rest of my life.

01:07:30.943 --> 01:07:33.111
Don't play around when it comes to her.

01:07:33.112 --> 01:07:34.780
I'm going to make everything okay.

01:07:34.781 --> 01:07:37.241
I'm scared. I'm terrified.

01:07:38.659 --> 01:07:40.118
I didn't know.

01:07:40.119 --> 01:07:43.080
Why? How could you not know?

01:07:43.081 --> 01:07:44.164
How about a date tomorrow?

01:07:44.165 --> 01:07:46.083
We can watch a movie, have a nice meal,

01:07:46.084 --> 01:07:48.210
and take a walk while we chat.

01:07:48.211 --> 01:07:49.711
We'll do what other couples do.

01:07:49.712 --> 01:07:51.963
Seonu Chan! Where are you?

01:07:51.964 --> 01:07:54.050
I'm so relieved nothing happened.

01:08:07.563 --> 01:08:08.647
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:08:08.648 --> 01:08:09.649
Translated by Juyoung Park
